==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tenesmus
<hw>Te*nes"mus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/, fr. <?/ to stretch: cf. L. <ets>tenesmos</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An urgent and distressing sensation, as if a
discharge from the intestines must take place, although none can be
effected; -- always referred to the lower extremity of the
rectum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Vesical tenesmus</b></col>, <cd>a similar sensation as to
the evacuation of urine, referred to the region of the
bladder.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tenet</ent>⟦br⟧
